    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<p><em>A gaunt woman with sharp features, long raven-black hair streaked with feathers, and piercing blue eyes that seem to glow faintly in darkness. She wears a dark, tattered robe adorned with crow feathers and carries a crooked staff resembling a talon.</em></p><h3>Personality</h3><p>Cryptic, observant, and slyly amused. Marla speaks in riddles and half-truths, always hinting she knows more than she reveals. She is careful whom she trusts, but delights in unsettling the overly bold.</p><h3>Motivation</h3><p>To protect ancient secrets of the city and maintain her delicate balance of power with unseen forces. She seeks knowledge, not dominance.</p><h3>Mannerisms</h3><p>Tilts her head like a bird when intrigued; absently twirls a feather between her fingers; speaks softly but pauses dramatically before unsettling revelations.</p><h3>Voice &amp; Accent</h3><p>Soft, airy, and eerily calm. She speaks slowly, as if savoring each word.</p><h3>Bonds, Ideals, Flaws</h3><ul><li><strong>Bond:</strong> Her pact with a neutral underworld entity binds her to safeguard the city's oldest oaths. She feels kinship with crows, who serve as her eyes and messengers.</li><li><strong>Ideal:</strong> Knowledge is power, but power must be veiled. The shadows hold truths that daylight cannot grasp.</li><li><strong>Flaw:</strong> Her obsession with forbidden knowledge blinds her to immediate dangers. She trusts her summoned allies more than living people.</li></ul><hr><h3>GM Notes</h3><p>Use Marla as a mysterious informant, quest-giver, or reluctant ally in city intrigue. Her knowledge is valuable, but her motives are layered. Spells: Eldritch Blast, Arms of Hadar, Misty Step, Suggestion.</p><h3>Secrets</h3><p>Marla knows of a sealed crypt nearby where undead have begun to rise, but she has not revealed its true origin. Her pact is with a neutral underworld watcher. Once every seven days she can activate a hidden summoning circle in her tower.</p><h3>Relationships</h3><p>Garron Vale: mutual suspicion. They have observed each other from afar during nocturnal patrols but remain wary and untrusting. City folk: fearful rumors about her tower lights and midnight rituals. Crows: messengers, spies, and symbolic companions.</p><h3>Plot Hooks</h3><p>1. Marla requests the party investigate the crypt where undead emerge.\n2. A stolen page from Marla's tome ends up in a rival's hands.\n3. Strange blue lights appear above the tower, attracting guards, cultists, and curious scholars.\n4. A summoned underworld entity asks the party for an unusual favor.\n5. Garron asks the party to find out what Marla is really summoning.</p><h3>Encounter Ideas</h3><p>1. Midnight meeting atop a rooftop to exchange secrets.\n2. Ritual interrupted by city guards, rival mages, or undead drawn to the tower.\n3. Crows deliver cryptic messages to the party.\n4. Exploration of the crypt Marla fears holds forgotten truths.</p>",
